  "A model rocket's height is h(t) = -16t^2 + 96t. Using the quadratic formula, find when the rocket hits the ground.": "",
  "3 seconds": "",
  "4 seconds": "",
  "6 seconds": "",
  "8 seconds": "",
  "Setting h(t) = 0: -16t^2 + 96t = 0. Using the quadratic formula: t = (-96 +/- sqrt(9216))/(-32) = (-96 +/- 96)/(-32). So t = 0 or t = -192/(-32) = 6 seconds.": "",
  "A rectangular pool's length is 3 meters more than twice its width. The area is 65 square meters. What is the width?": "",
