  "5 meters": "",
  "Let w = width: w(2w + 3) = 65, so 2w^2 + 3w - 65 = 0. Using the formula: w = (-3 +/- sqrt(9 + 520))/4 = (-3 +/- 23)/4. Taking the positive: w = 20/4 = 5 meters.": "",
  "A baseball is hit with height h(t) = -16t^2 + 64t + 4. Using the discriminant, determine how many times the ball reaches a height of 68 feet.": "",
